                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d488">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">339.115 General Motors Export Co./9:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-19T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 19, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. Reference Department’s telegram No. 10 April 19, 6 p.m.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d488fn3">Not printed.</note> Penn Tobacco Company has communicated
                    further with the Department referring to the urgent cable received today from
                        Marcus<note n="3a" xml:id="d488fn3a">Manager of Dominican Tobacco
                        Company.</note> and requesting that you “cable full confidential report from
                    Marcus on situation with reason for his request”. You are authorized to cable
                    such message.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
